This paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for detecting ransomware attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the use of decision tree classifiers, which is a common machine learning technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The dataset used in the study is based on network traffic features, which falls under the category of network and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of ransomware attacks on various industries, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
